HEADWORD: parse
<hw>parse</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧rs)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>parsed</conjf> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧rst)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>parsing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>pars</ets>
a part; <ets>pars orationis</ets> a part of speech. See <er>Part</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>To resolve into its
elements, as a sentence, pointing out the several parts of speech, and
their relation to each other by government or agreement; to analyze and
describe grammatically.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let him construe the letter into English, and <qex>parse</qex> it
over perfectly.</q> <rj><qau>Ascham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>parsec</ent>⟦br⟧
